    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Dipeptide-86 s-Paper Wasp Thr6-Bradykinin Hexapeptide-1 Amide is a single chain fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from Dipeptide-86 and s-Paper Wasp Thr6-Bradykinin Hexapeptide-1, in which the C-terminus is an amide. The fusion peptide contains 8 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
